      "source": [
        "**ML Model Training: Predicting the Profitability and Sales**"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "bPgDcGuNOBAu"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "Model 1: Linear Regression Model"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "cN9W2DVMK2Og"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "Note: Since there is no date column in the dataset, the Multivariate Linear Regression Model will be implemented on a transactional level using One-Hot Encoding to convert text columns (like Category and Region) into numerical inputs that the model can understand."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "zQfy-WUhOiAB"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "Part 1: Model Training & Evaluation Metrics Table\n",
        "\n",
        "This block is the mathematical engine of the modeling process. It maps the features using One-Hot Encoding, splits the dataset into training (80%) and validation (20%) sets, trains two separate Multivariate Linear Regression models, and outputs the definitive numeric validation table ($R^2$, MSE, RMSE, MAE) requested by Objective 3."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "ueqVJDRFfKcB"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n",
        "from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression\n",
        "from sklearn.metrics import r2_score, mean_squared_error, mean_absolute_error\n",
        "\n",
        "# --- 1. FEATURE SELECTION ---\n",
        "categorical_features = ['Ship_Mode', 'Segment', 'Region', 'Category', 'Sub-Category']\n",
        "numerical_features = ['Quantity', 'Discount']\n",
        "\n",
        "# Apply One-Hot Encoding to convert categorical text to numerical binary flags (0 or 1)\n",
